WLC_KEYBOARD_GET_CURRENT_KEYS(3)                         WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_keyboard_get_current_keys - get list of currently held keys

SYNOPSIS

    const uint32_t* wlc_keyboard_get_current_keys(size_t *out_count);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_keyboard_get_current_keys() is used to list all the currently held keys
    which is primarily used to detect a correct combinations of keys have been
    pressed.  The out_count parameter is set to the number of keys pressed.

RETURN VALUE

    wlc_keyboard_get_current_keys() returns an array of keys pressed.
